4.10	Pulicat_Lake	Pulicat Lake	Pulicat Lake (Telugu: Pulicat Sarassu పులికాట్ సరస్సు, Tamil: Pazhaverkaadu Eri பழவேற்காடு ஏரி ) is the second largest brackish – water lake or lagoon in India. It straddles the border of Andhra Pradesh and Tamil Nadu states on the Coromandal Coast in South India. The lake encompasses the Pulicat Lake Bird Sanctuary. The barrier island of Sriharikota separates the lake from the Bay of Bengal. The island is home to the Satish Dhawan Space Centre.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cc/India_-_Pulicat_Lake_-_023_-_lake_landscape.jpg/240px-India_-_Pulicat_Lake_-_023_-_lake_landscape.jpg
